This paper is about learning Bayesian network structures from data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a new algorithm for finding the k-best Bayesian network structures and using Bayesian model averaging to compute posterior probabilities. This work is closely related to topics in machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), statistical inference (cs.SI), and information theory (cs.IT).
